ne Jury gestellt und in regulären Gefängnissen inhaftiert. Doch auch die Strategie der Kriminalisierung scheiterte. In den Gefängnissen entflammten Proteste, die die Legitimität des britischen Rechtsstaats mehr denn je infrage stellten.  aIn the late 1960s, there was unrest between the Catholic minority and the Protestant majority in Northern Ireland. Andreas Spreier examines how the British legal state reacted to the political violence by looking at state court and internment policies, which transformed from the use of the military and internment without legal proceedings into the criminalization of the IRA by means of the police and justice system.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 4aIrish Republican Army. 4aRechtsstaat. 4aTerrorismus. 4aThe Troubles. 4aVereinigtes Königreich Großbritannien und Nordirland. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Great Britain / General.2bisacsh  aIrish Republican Arms The Troubles.  aUnited Kingdom of Great Britain and Northern Ireland.  alegal state.  aterrorism.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2024 Part 1z97831113321920 cEPUBz97831107745040 cprintz978311077422140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311077440540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110774405423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110774405/original  a978-3-11-133219-2  DG Plus DeG Package 2024 Part 1b2024  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles